The paper proposes a solution for runtime enforcement of critical properties in reactive hardware systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Embedded Systems (cs.ET) sub-category. However, the paper also discusses the challenges of runtime enforcement in reactive systems, which could place it in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the synthesis of a safety shield, which could relate to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. The paper also mentions reactive synthesis, which could place it in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experimental results, which could relate to the Architecture (cs.AR) sub-category.
